{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018hAzrg1QBtTqTdYJCrMsQa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The case:\n\n1. **Precondition**: Checks if the cluster is already running (via StatefulSet or Running pods). If the cluster exists, it SKIPS the apply step. This is the pattern - the existing cluster from stage 01-04 is preserved.\n\n2. **Oracle**: `python3 cases/cockroachdb/partitioned-update/oracle/oracle.py`\n\nLet me read the oracle to understand what checks it runs!\n\nAlso, the apply step (which was SKIPPED because the cluster already existed) includes `kubectl -n cockroachdb apply -f cases/cockroachdb/partitioned-update/resource/`. \n\nThe apply step would have deployed the resource manifest for this case. Looking at the verification logic, I see it's checking for secure vs insecure mode - the init command uses `--insecure`, indicating this case is meant to run in insecure mode. The verify step is more sophisticated though: it first checks if certificates exist, and if they do, it switches to using the certs directory instead of the insecure flag.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1799,"cache_read_input_tokens":85312,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1799},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9890bff2-62c4-4c97-b1f2-1767ee9bac2a","uuid":"6d2b6162-76fa-4809-8cea-aa5cc102d2d2","request_id":"req_011CcMcLKtSkBrjqeAhXGVJE"}
